VENTERSDORP - A six-metre-tall bronze statue of John Marks has been unveiled at Ventersdorp in the North West Province.Marks is considered by many as a hero of the working class and the country s liberation struggle.His remains were reburied in Ventersdorp in 2015.READ: Welcome home, JB MarksMarks died in 1972 in Moscow after suffering a heart attack.He served as chairman of the South African Communist Party and was a member of the National Executive Committee of the ANC.The site on which Marks' remains were reburied and his statue erected have been declared a heritage site.eNCA